publishLabelOptions.displayName: RequestCount - Scale:60 - Mean(1h) - Sum by LoadBalancer
publishLabelOptions.label: A

chart.programText:
A = data('RequestCount', filter=filter('AvailabilityZone', '*') and filter('LoadBalancer', '*') and filter('stat', 'sum') and filter('namespace', 'AWS/ApplicationELB'), extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=5).scale(60).mean(over='1h').sum(by=['LoadBalancer']).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = (A).timeshift('1w').publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (A/B-1).scale(100).publish(label='C')

chart.name: # of Active Connections
chart.programText: A = data('ActiveConnectionCount', filter=filter('namespace', 'AWS/ApplicationELB') and filter('stat', 'sum'), rollup='latest').sum().publish(label='A')

chart.name: LBs with Highest Unhealthy Host %
chart.programText:
A = data('HealthyHostCount', filter=filter('AvailabilityZone', '*') and filter('LoadBalancer', '*') and filter('stat', 'mean') and filter('namespace', 'AWS/ApplicationELB'), extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=5).sum(by=['LoadBalancer']).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('UnHealthyHostCount', filter=filter('AvailabilityZone', '*') and filter('LoadBalancer', '*') and filter('stat', 'mean') and filter('namespace', 'AWS/ApplicationELB'), extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=5).sum(by=['LoadBalancer']).publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (B/(A+B)).scale(100).publish(label='C')

chart.programText: A = data('HTTPCode_T*', filter=filter('namespace', 'AWS/ApplicationELB') and filter('stat', 'sum') and filter('LoadBalancer', 'app/pops-us-west-2/e8a5a160c16dba54')).sum(by=['TargetGroup']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Number of TLS connections initiated by the load balancer that did not establish a session with the target. Possible causes include a mismatch of ciphers or protocols.

chart.description: Total number of concurrent TCP connections active from clients to the load balancer and from the load balancer to targets.
chart.name: # of Active Connections
Target response time Over Last Minute
chart.programText:
A = data('TargetResponseTime', filter=filter('AvailabilityZone', '*') and filter('stat', 'mean') and filter('LoadBalancer', '*') and filter('namespace', 'AWS/ApplicationELB'), extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=5).sum(by=['LoadBalancer']).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = (A).min().publish(label='B')
C = (A).percentile(pct=10).publish(label='C')
D = (A).percentile(pct=50).publish(label='D')
E = (A).percentile(pct=90).publish(label='E')
F = (A).max().publish(label='F')
